article.headline: Murray State 73, Eastern Illinois 69
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Trey Pearson made six 3-pointers and scored 23 points to lead Murray State to a 73-69 victory over Eastern Illinois on Thursday night. Reggie Jackson added 18 points and six rebounds for the Racers (12-7, 7-2 Ohio Valley Conference), who won for the fifth time in six games. Pearson also had four assists for Murray State, which has won five in a row at home. Emanuel Dildy scored 15 points and George Tandy added 14 for Eastern Illinois (8-12, 3-6), which lost despite shooting 50 percent from the field. The Racers were 9-of-23 from 3-point range (39 percent).
